public environment seminar requirements page 1 public environment seminar requirements 1 students are expected to attend all meetings of the public environmental seminar 341 343 2 students who are on the job market are expected to present a seminar during the fall quarter 3 other advanced students may present a seminar as well 4 all students attend all meetings of the applied micro lunch group follow the rules of that lunch group and schedule regular presentations at the lunch fourth year students are expected to present in the fall quarter unless there is a scarcity of slots available 5 students must meet regularly to discuss their research with a faculty member who regularly attends the public environmental seminar and or applied micro lunch this faculty member need not be the student's primary advisor 6 students are strongly encouraged to attend at least one other seminar or reading group 7 students are strongly encouraged to meet with the seminar speaker when they are invited to do so
